      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cover the <strong>chicken breast portions</strong> in <strong>cling film</strong> and bash with a <strong>rolling pin </strong>until flattened to approx. 1cm thickness then season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate, a splash of <strong>milk </strong>to a shallow bowl and your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to a separate plate</p><p>Coat the <strong>flattened chicken</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off any excess, then add it into the <strong>milk</strong> and finally press it into the <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> firmly to evenly coat all over</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
